    "causal_summary": "The Phase 018 R4 shared-payload envelope (`createSharedPayloadEnvelope()` / `coerceSharedPayloadEnvelope()` in `mcp_server/lib/context/shared-payload.ts`) currently accepts producer and source enums covering code-graph, startup-brief, and compact-recovery surfaces. It has no first-class `advisor` producer or advisor-metadata shape. Without extending the envelope, later children (004 producer, 005 renderer, 006-008 runtime adapters) would either overload an unrelated producer enum or bypass the shared transport. Wave-1 §Pattern Parallel Map and wave-2 X9 both require the envelope to reject prompt-derived provenance and to carry only typed advisor fields (freshness, confidence, uncertainty, sanitized label).",
